# authwatch authorized_keys allowlist.
#
# One entry per line, each either:
#   - an OpenSSH SHA256 fingerprint (as printed by `ssh-keygen -lf <pubkey>`), or
#   - a full public-key line (authwatch computes its fingerprint).
#
# Any authorized_keys entry whose fingerprint is NOT listed here is reported as
# an unattributable key (T1098.004). Keep this file on the off-host trust anchor
# or otherwise read-only, and regenerate it deliberately when you add a key.

# Fingerprint form:
SHA256:n0tAr3alF1ngerpr1ntJustShowingTheFormatHere000000000000

# Full public-key form:
ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAEXAMPLEonlyNOTaRealKey00000000000 max@trusted-laptop
